<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08176f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08176f">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08176f"> 176(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> in 6 months / makes counties / circuit judges / Sets up K&apos;s bench / pleas / exchequer / tithes arranged</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Henry had been only six months in Ireland, but he had accomplished much&mdash;more certainly than any other English ruler ever accomplished afterwards within the same time. He had divided the ceded territories into counties; had appointed sheriffs for them; had set up the Law Courts&mdash;Bench, Pleas and Exchequer; had arranged for the going on circuit by judges; and had established his own character for orthodoxy, and acquitted himself of his obligations to the papacy by freeing all church property from the exactions of the chiefs, and rigidly enforcing the payment of tithes. <small> Emily Lawless, <a name="ELIS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ELIS"><cite title="source">Ireland (Story of Nations series</cite></a> (192?) 93</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
